{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_92","type":"agent_message","text":"The per-key test-config workaround is turning into a bad loop because the real problem is still “Akka defaults aren’t being loaded in native-image.” I’m changing tactics: the Akka test project will now copy `reference.conf` and `version.conf` directly from the Akka runtime JARs into test resources, then load them through a tiny test-local `reference.conf`. That keeps the fix scoped to this generated test project and avoids hardcoding more of Akka’s defaults in Scala."}}
